## Port type connectability (Studio catalog)

Edges are allowed only when both handles resolve to a `StudioNodePortValueType` (YAML catalog and/or handle `portValueType` on descriptors, including dynamic nodes and patch slots). **`studioPortValueTypesConnectable`** and **`tryCatalogPortConnection`** / **`canConnect`** in `ui/editor/nodeHelpers.ts` implement:

- Same type → connectable (audio–audio, trigger–trigger, bool–bool, enum–enum).
- `int` ↔ `float` → connectable (numeric CV).

There is no separate legacy path: if either handle has no resolved port type, the connection is rejected.

**`isAudioConnection`** (edge styling / audio-rate routing hints) is true only when **both** ends resolve to `audio`.
